The paper discusses a cheating strategy in Massive Open Online Courses (MOOCs) and uses clickstream learner data to detect its prevalence. This suggests a focus on cybersecurity (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for detecting cheating. The paper also discusses preventive strategies, which could fall under the categories of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computational social science (cs.CY). Additionally, the use of clickstream data could involve natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques for analyzing user behavior.
